                "invention-title": [
                    "Low-temperature carbon capture process for gas shift in hydrogen production from natural gas",
                    "一种用于天然气制氢中变气的低温碳捕集工艺"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to a low-temperature carbon capture process for natural gas hydrogen production medium shift gas, which is composed of a CO2 liquefaction separation module, a CO2 desublimation separation module and a refrigeration system, and is characterized in that the medium shift gas is compressed and pre-cooled to be partially liquefied, and then enters a gas-liquid separator to separate liquid CO2; the gas-phase part enters a gas-solid separator with a cooling function to be continuously cooled, CO2 is separated from the gas-phase part in a solid dry ice mode in a desublimation mode, and purified gas with the CO2 content reduced to 0.2% or below is obtained; cold energy required by the system is provided by low-temperature purified gas and an independent vapor compression type mixed refrigerant refrigeration cycle; compared with the prior art, the method has the advantages that absorption or adsorption equipment which occupies a large area in conventional medium-shift gas carbon capture is omitted, and the investment cost in the process of producing hydrogen from natural gas can be greatly reduced; by combining the technical means of liquefaction and desublimation, the energy consumption of low-temperature carbon capture can be effectively reduced while the CO2 capture rate is remarkably improved."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及一种用于天然气制氢中变气的低温碳捕集工艺，由CO2液化分离模块、CO2凝华分离模块和制冷系统组成，中变气经压缩、预冷至部分液化后进入气液分离器中分离出液态的CO2；气相部分接着进入带冷却的气固分离器继续降温，CO2以固体干冰的形式从中变气中凝华分离出来，得到CO2含量降至0.2％以下的净化气；系统所需的冷量由低温净化气和一个独立的蒸汽压缩式混合制冷剂制冷循环提供；与现有技术相比，本发明省去了常规中变气碳捕集占地面积很大的吸收或吸附设备，可大大降低天然气制氢过程的投资成本；结合液化和凝华的技术手段在显著提高CO2捕集率的同时可有效降低低温碳捕集的能耗。"
                }
            ]
